es at super-Eddington rate of $1.17-1.31~\n\\dot{M}_{\\rm Edd}$. Moreover, we find the mass and spin of the source as $12.44\n- 13.09~M_{\\odot}$ and $0.990-0.997$ with $90\\%$ confidence suggesting that GRS\n1915$+$105 is a maximally rotating stellar mass X-ray binary black hole source.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 8 Oct 2020 05:58:00 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-11-18"}
