0^{\\circ}$ phase angle. We detected a low non-zero specular\nratio, perhaps indicating exposed sub-centimeter mono-crystalline inclusions on\nthe surface. We report an average roughness RMS slope of $27_{-5}^{\\circ+1}$, a\nspecular ratio of $2.6_{-0.8}^{+0.1}\\%$, an approx. single-scattering albedo of\n$4.64_{-0.09}^{+0.08}\\%$ at 550 nm, and two solutions for the back-scatter\nasymmetric factor, $\\xi^{(1)}=-0.360\\pm0.030$ and $\\xi^{(2)}=-0.444\\pm0.020$,\nfor all four sites altogether.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 8 Oct 2020 14:57:09 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-10-09"}
